<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Hi! I am a lvl 12 Paladin and I saw your message asking for lvling tips etc.. I also noticed a reply to it... I have to tell you I disagree with the reply. Paladins are not difficult to play if you know how to play it. Before you reach lvl 9 you are a essentially a warrior, no u dont have the hp's a warrior has but you come mighty close if you practice right. Look in the EQ Stats book they will agree with me when i say that a Paladin has very much the same stats as a Warrior mixed with some Cleric. That's because that is what a Paladin is.. a hybrid between a Warrior and a Cleric.<p>

You need to concentrate on your melee skills... dont ever rely on your casting because you dont recive them often and when you do they heals aren't worth a whole lot and the buffs arent either although if you are soloing the buffs work great for yourself they have gotten many a Paladin through some tuff times. The best casting spell u have is the Lay Hands spell that u begin the game with. You can only use it once every game day which is about an hour and a half real time. avoid using this spell on anyone else unless you are in a group u feel confident in. It's for emergency use and is best used for yourself when a healer doesnt see your health or can't heal you due to low mana.<br>
You can solo very well! I used a 1hs weapon until about lvl 6 where I received a 2hs weapon from a friendly player who donated it to me at no cost. You can't rely on this kind of help but dont be afraid to ask as long as yo not a pest people dont mind the shouts ie "lvl 7 Pally, would like a nice weapon to help him/her out, can donate what money I have" i have a full set of bronze armour and a 2hs slash weapon thats base damage is 17 and usally hist around 28, 90% of what i have was given to me by different people along the way.<p>

SOLOING:: When you enter a zone use the /who feature and check everyones lvls, if there is quite a few people of your lvl chances are its a good place to be, if evryone seems lowere leave you wont get much exp, and if everyone seems higher, leave because its most likely too dangerous for you. Solo when you can (paladins are great soloists) and use the /con feature.. /con everything! If you are solo attack blue things but try to bring them near a zone, so that if you need to run you can. Blue npcs will award the most exp to a solo pally, just make sure you have a plan b because like it tells you.. you might win (there is a chance for loss), avoid fighting at lower lvls with anything less than about 90% health, just because it cons green doesnt mean u can fight it with less than a bubbles health always keep that in mind...<p>

GROUPING:<br>
Paladins are also a very good grouper, groups are always willing to invite a pally due to your abilities as a puller and in case of emergency a healer.  A good ratios is this.. dont ever try to be a healer. If you are in a small group that has no healer, nobody should continue to fight when they become low on health, dont expect ot heal them with your heals they dont do much trust me. You are mostly considered a tank, at any given lvl you will have higher hp than other classes of the smae lvl with the exception of the warrior they will have a higher hp,so you are mostly used as a tank unless there happens to be a warrior in the group which even then you are still a tank but rather a backup to the warrior.. Leave the healing to the primary casters such as clerics... try to group with clerics or their healing, druids for their ability to hold a target still while you fight another which comes in very handy when tackling lare groups of enemies, and rangers for their ability to reack an enemy (find it for you). As far as what to fight in a group a group can easily fight what is red to the group members as long as they come one at a time.. Blues can be brought in several at a time if your group is big enough. <p>

PULLING:<br>
Get a cheap bow and some basic arrows, place this in your range wapon and ammo slots on your inventory screens.. these come in very ahndy when you are soloing or are in a group. The reason is that if you run into a group of enemies and do the typical attack, and run tactic to bring the enemy to your group 9 times outta 10 the entire group of enemies will come with you which is fine i fyou have a druid or the like around to"hold" the others for you but if not youdont wanna bring a big group of enemies with you, no matter what they /con a large group is tuff to handle.. With the bow and arrow you cans tay a safe distance away froma  creature and shoot it. Stay put and the creature will run by itself to you and away from the mob where you can safely attack, and run tacic to bring it the rest of the way to your group or if you are soloingyou can bring it back near a zone or other safe place. Dont worry about getting expensive bows or arrows its not yor main attack, you dont need high dmg with them because even the slightest prick of an arrow will irritate the enemy enough to chase you. <p>

1HS vs 2HS:<br>
Do not allocate your abilities evenly between 1hs and 2hs weapons, this will limit your abilitys in noth skills. You need to find one you like and stick to it... Consider this: 1hs has less delay (you attack faster) but less damage (your hits dont hurt the npcs as much)--2hs weapons have a higher delay (you attack slower-more time in between hits) but they award more per hit damage (your hits cause more damage)... <br>
My advice is to get a good 1hs weapon and use it only until you can find a 2hs weapon.. ask around, be friendly to higher lvl players and try to get yourself a good 2hs weapon, yes the delay is slower but as you get into higher lvls the delay will shorten and your hitpoints will be what you are worried about. If you didn't know, just because a weapon says its dmg 10 or in my case 17 does not mean thats what dmg it wil do. when you begin to use the wapon it will vary from much lower than the base dmg to a little higher than the base dmage, the more u youse it the better your skill gets, the better your skill gets the more accurate you become and the mor focuse dyoru hps become and like mine which base dmg is 17 and hits around 28, you will surpass your weapons base hp.. This doesnt work for all weapons of the category though.. by this I mean thta if you need to pick not only one category such as 1hs or 2hs but you need to find a good weapon from that category and stick to it. You may have heard that u  must be a certain lvl to use a 2hs weapon, this is not true. The thing is until you reach a certain lvl u cannot go to your trainer adn train with that category (2hs slash), but you can however improve by simply using the weapon  which is much more effective anyway.<p>

Using Spells:<br>
Never rely on your spells!!! If youre soloing put your courage buff on anad whatever other buffs you have, watch the chat bar to look for nearby higher lvl player who are giving buffs they will usally donate for no charge. At lvl 9 your best spells are yaulp (a spell that increases your dmg temporarily while fighting), flash of light (blinds the target temporarily make it  easier for you to attack it and preventing it from attacking you) and courage (a buff that hads to your hp and ac). I know ive mentioned it but dont rely on your minor healing spell to save you.. it is exactly what it says.. minor, very minor, the time it takes u to cast a creature  has time to attack u for more than the heal spell will replace. You are a good melee fighter, use that to your advantage and use the flash of light and yaulps in your attacks, when your fighting something that cons blue or abpve use the yaulp and flash of light constantly! hit the yaulp then the flash of light then kepp alternating between the two. This works very well.<p>

LEVELING:<br>
I find that once you achieve lvl 7 or 8 yo can get a lot of exp by grouping and fighting in Crushbone often referred to as CB). Like I said earlier use the /who command but do it more specifically. Do not join a group where there will be more than 3 recurring lvls in it (dont join a group thats lvls 14,10, and 8 or 12-8... stick with the ones that are 7,8 and 9 or 10-12, etc), if you get into a lvl gapped group that contains more than 3 lvls such as 14, 13, and 10, the exp will get messed up and nobody will get their fair share. Usally the higher lvls get the most of the exp so stick with people around your lvl. Use the /who command to see who is in your area and in your lvl be specific if you are lvl 8 use, /who 8 or /who 9 or /who 10 to try to get a group thats 8-10 or do the /who 6 or /who 7 or /who 8 to get a group thats lvl 6-8.. This /who system helps out greatly once you see that there are players within the lvlsyou need send tells.. dont rely on someone responding to your shout for a group although you should do that as well..So Send tells to those in the lvls you need and shouts for a group. When soloing fight blue things near a safe place at full health and when in a group get a healer and fight groups of blue items or single red items... avoid fighting things that con green to you they award the least exp (if any).. generally once you start getting less (to none) loot form corpses its time to move on to something stronger.. Avoid death, that takes away exp the more u die th emore exp it takes away when u do. <p>

If you have any questions you can reply here or email me SmilesInCal@aol.com or contact me in game, I fight in Crushbone most of the time on weekends.. the characters name is Laurelie (High Elf Paladin) and the guild is Clerics of Norrath (they accept all classes above lvl 10, soon will be upping it to minimum lvl 25) the guild name should help ya see me but just look around an ddo some /who commands... hope this helps you out and like i said fell free to contact me.. the tactics I have described have worked and continue to work wonderfully for me.. I only play on weekends yet seem to lvl as fast if nto fast than people in my class who play much more often.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
