<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Hail all honorable paladins!<p>

Personally, I love the paladin class. Difficult at some points, but the overall reward is great if you play the paladin as close to the paladin spirit as you can. In other words, do every paladin quest that you can, even if the item is worse than something you already have.<p>

Here are some good low level quests:<p>

1. Shining Star of Light 1HB 6/26, proc Cleanse (paladin/cleric only.) Great quest weapon...almost as good as screaming mace.<br>
Good weapon, especially for  for paladins/clerics under 20th season. Good to keep up 1hb after 25 still. Quest is easy, but you have to kill a lot of WK bandits and turn in their sashes for the right faction.<p>

2. Bonethunder Staff 2hb 9/36 +3 WIS procs: Ward Undead...paladin/cleric only NODROP.<br>
Another great quest item for paladins/clerics only. The quest is very easy, but may need help killing the mammoth in Surefall Glade (hes 20) or you have to run to Ak anon to get the vomit potion for the mamoth to caugh up the quest item.<p>

3. Falchion of Koada'Vie. Good 1hs weapon, paladin only. The quest is a little tougher than the other two quests, since it involves a box from 1 of 3 low 20s creatures in Ocean of Tears, Dvinn's heart and Emporor Crush's head or something. <p>

All 3 of those quests are for good paladin only weapons that are great for mid teens and early 20s.<p>

But I HIGHLY recommend doing the Shining Star of Light and the Bonethunder Staff quests...they both raise the faction required for Armor of Ro and Soulfire quests. Once you are able to do those quests, your Qenos faction will be good enough for Soulfire and Armor of Ro....so you only have to work on your Freeport and other paladin factions.<p>

Besides, the bonethunder is +3 wis and procs a 41pt DD undead spell...great weapon! Shining Star of Light procs cleanse, which helps to remove Poison/Disease/root and other dots. I still use SSoL and Bonethunder in my mid 30s to keep up my 1hb/2hb skills.<p>

<br>
Especaily if you are new to EQ, do the quests. They will help keep your equipment upgraded. Buying equipment is hard as a new player, since you don't know the best places to hunt and earn coin yet.<p>

Hope this helps, and always feel free to ask for help on quests!<p>

Rotep<br>
Human Paladin<br>
Mid 30s - Veeshan</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
