<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Hail Brother and well met,<p>

     The wisdom that Lord Marr has imparted to me in my journeys to right Norrath of Evils blight!<br>
            1. Remeber you are a servant of light and as such must conduct yourself in acccordance with the code of your temple! <p>

 ( This means several things, one always always aways help others even if you know it will cost you! Why, you will be pleasently suprised later in your career to have a deep red con player visit you and talk to you about how you LOH him or how you started him out with good equipment when he started his character. In my time in the game i have been passed by several players i knew, im not a powergamer or a twink and im not a player who can spend the many hours i would like to playing. But i have made many friends that are always willing to help because i held the horde while they got away!  This doesnt imply be stupid and die on every encounter but you will know when it is time for the heroic pally death, when it is time for you to LOH your group mate and save the day, BE SELFLESS it will pay off when you least expect it!)<p>

<br>
          2. Learn your trade, never favor the blade when one day your God may hand you the Mace!<p>

           ( Point here is max all of your skills out NOW and keep them their, this will make your character more usefull and rounded than probably 90% of the others youll encounter in the game. Think about it how many times have you seen the ubber troll warrior standing over a lvl 30 HighHold Gob mob asking if he cn practice his 2h bash because the skill is only 16 when it could possibly be maxed at 225? Ive seen it often in fact im paying the price of still developing my skills to max at 40th. Specifically, got down time swim, need to work on divination cast a spell repeatdly until it increases, etc..etc... just keep track of your skills and try to train on them each as you level this will pay major dividends for you later believe me. I wont go into weapons selections just aquire one of each type and hunt with them when you get one skill maxed switch weapons to get the next maxed etc..etc... REMEBER KNIGHTS WERE REQUIRED TO TRAIN IN ALL WEAPONS)<p>

     3.Know your enemy just as you would your companions!<p>

         ( Well this sounds very general like hehehehehe....anyways my point here is this dont get caught in the routine while your grouping of tank, tank, tank, tank  learn what parts each of the people you are grouping with do, find out how they would tackle the situation this will open your knowledge of the game up so that you will know instintaviley what to do to best help your group! Dont play into the Mobs hands that your fighting! example I watched a Pally soloing dead he would walk up to mummys in N Ro and stand Toe to Toe with them swinging away until he or they dropped, he ran to the guards a few times to be saved, when he came back i asked him if he had the spook the dead spell? when he said yes i showed him how to fear kite{spook mummy, chase mummy while it runs and beat on it}. Im not the brightest guy in the world and in fact someone had to show me the same trick when i was a younger Paladin and as you can imagine his downtime decreased and subsequently he leveled faster. Really the more you learn from other the more youll benefit in the game. Think out of the Box JUST BECAUSE YOUR A KNIGHT IT DOES NOT MEAN YOUR GOING TO WIN BY STANDING TOE TO TOE WITH YOUR FOE!<p>

          All of the articles above have great points and ring with truths! The most important thing to remeber is TO THINE SELF BE TRUE! You brother are a Paladin a great calling that many cannot accept (e.g. why paladin my warrior is much better, etc..etc...)<br>
We are a brotherhood and will always be!<p>

          May Lord Marr grant you strength in your task, Sir Sonodar!<br>
           ( Or whatever god you worship)<br>
          /em salutes you!<br>
          /says Now off to slay those windmills.....err i mean giants!<br>
          /shouts CHARGE!!!!<br>
          /em think to himself "why are all these gnomes standing on these giants feet?"<hr>Ceddrick Peredhil<br>
Paladin 40 season<br>
Rallos Zek</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
